README.md

#0
# File->New | Open | Open Recent-> | Close | Save | Save As... | Backup |
#   Dump | Import (e.g., from CSV/TSV/etc) | Export (e.g. to ditto) | Quit
#1 pure SQL
#2 custom types via Tcl functions (e.g., tobytes, frombytes, tosring)
#3 custom forms
#4 custom layouts (i.e., for 'apps')
#  Ideally support vsplit & hsplit for tabs so that I can show two tabs
#  side-by-side and/or above-below i.e., 1, 2, 3, or 4 tabs visible at
#  the same time.
#5 ultimately aim to be able to replace both Biller and Notebox with
#  custom songbird databases

# SDI one main window per db
# Main window layout:
#
#   Menu bar.................
#   Tool bar.................
#   Contents tree is a dock window
#   Central area is MDI for Form/List views
#   Status bar.....................

# &File              &Edit        &Options	        &SQL
#   &New... ^N         &Copy ^C     [X] Show &Toolbar     Create &SELECT...
#   &Open... ^O        Cu&t  ^X     [X] Show &Contents    ---------
#   Open &Recent ->    &Paste ^V    [ ] Show C&alendar    Create &Table...
#   &Save ^S                        [ ] Show Calc&ulator  Create &View...
#   Save &As...                     ------------------    &Create Trigger...
#   &Backup...                      &Toggle Form|List     ---------
#   ---------                       ------------------    &Alter Table...
#   &Import...                      &Options...           Alter Vie&w...
#   &Export...                                            A&lter Trigger...
#   ---------                       
#   &Close F4
#   &Quit ^Q

# &Form                &Window                 &Help
#   &Next F6             &Next Alt+F6            &About
#   &Previous Shift+F6   &Previous Shift+Alt+F6  &Help F1
#   &1 <mdi name>        &1 <window name>                   
#      :	            :                               
#   &9 <mdi name>        &9 <window name>
#   &More ->             &More ->
#   ---------            ---------
#   &Close Shift+F4      &Close Alt+F4          

# Initially insert/update can only be done in form view and delete in
# form or list view. Ideally allow in-place insert/update in list view
# if/when possible.

